            <title>[CAMEL-2238] JettyHttpProducer - Sending sync using waitForDone should cater for connection failures</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2238</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Even though we follow the Jetty documentation it will make the jetty http producer appear as blocked as &lt;tt&gt;waitForDone()&lt;/tt&gt; will block when connection failure occurred.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to add logic which polls the status instead and thus can detect the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The async producer &lt;b&gt;done not&lt;/b&gt; have this issue by which is likely the main use case for using Jetty as a client&lt;/p&gt;</description>
